# 💬 Console Chat Application (Java + JDBC)

## 📌 Project Description
A real-time console-based Chat Application developed using Java Socket Programming and Multithreading.
The application allows multiple clients to communicate with a server, and messages are stored in a database using JDBC.

## 🚀 Features
- Client-Server Architecture
- Real-time Messaging
- Multi-client support using Multithreading
- Message storage using JDBC (MySQL)
- Login system (optional)
- Persistent chat history

## 🛠 Concepts Used
- Socket Programming (ServerSocket, Socket)
- Multithreading
- JDBC (Database Connectivity)
- OOP Principles
- Exception Handling

## 🗄 Database
- MySQL database for storing chat messages
- Table:
  - id
  - sender
  - message
  - timestamp

## ▶ How to Run
1. Start the Server
2. Run multiple Client instances
3. Connect clients to server (localhost, port)
4. Start chatting

